data.current_description:
Schedules a new payment to be created (including a new authorisation request) for the specified donation using the payment details of the original payment.

This endpoint is part of our [classic API integration](https://docs.adyen.com/online-payments/classic-integrations/api-integration-ecommerce). If using a [newer integration](https://docs.adyen.com/online-payments), use the [`/donations`](https://docs.adyen.com/api-explorer/#/CheckoutService/latest/post/donations) endpoint under Checkout API instead.
data.summary_suggestion: Schedule a donation payment using original payment details
data.description_suggestion: Schedules a new payment and authorization request for a donation using the payment details from the original payment. This creates a new transaction linked to the donor's original payment method. Returns a unique reference for the donation transaction. Supports recurring donations by reusing stored payment credentials.
data.reasoning: Original summary 'Create a donation' is too generic and doesn't clarify that this reuses original payment details. Description lacks clarity on what 'donation' means in payment context and doesn't explain the return value or use case. Added specificity about payment reuse, authorization, and return value for better AI agent understanding.

data.current_description: Retrieves the `threeDS2Result` after doing a 3D Secure 2 authentication only.
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves the 3D Secure 2 (3DS2) authentication result after a customer completes the 3DS2 challenge. This endpoint is used to obtain the authentication outcome and result data following a 3DS2 authentication flow. Requires the 3DS2 session reference or authentication identifier from the initial authentication request. Returns the authentication status, result code, and cryptographic proof of authentication.

message: Operation 'post-voidPendingRefund' has semantic quality issues: vague_summary, missing_output_details. Summary 'Cancel an in-person refund' is misleading - the operation works for both online and offline refunds, not just in-person. Description lacks output details and doesn't clarify the 'unreferenced' concept. Added clarity that this cancels pending refunds before completion, emphasized the recommended tenderReference approach, and included return value information for better AI agent understanding.

data.current_description:
This endpoint allows you to cancel an unreferenced refund request before it has been completed.

In your call, you can refer to the original refund request either by using the `tenderReference`, or the `pspReference`. We recommend implementing based on the `tenderReference`, as this is generated for both offline and online transactions.

For more information, refer to [Cancel an unreferenced refund](https://docs.adyen.com/point-of-sale/refund-payment/cancel-unreferenced).
data.summary_suggestion: Cancel a pending unreferenced refund request
data.description_suggestion: Cancels an unreferenced refund request before it completes, preventing the refund from being processed. Can reference the original refund using either `tenderReference` (recommended for both online and offline transactions) or `pspReference`. Returns confirmation of the cancellation and the refund status. Only applicable to refunds that have not yet been completed.
data.reasoning: Summary 'Cancel an in-person refund' is misleading - the operation works for both online and offline refunds, not just in-person. Description lacks output details and doesn't clarify the 'unreferenced' concept. Added clarity that this cancels pending refunds before completion, emphasized the recommended tenderReference approach, and included return value information for better AI agent understanding.

data.current_description:
This endpoint allows you to cancel an unreferenced refund request before it has been completed.

In your call, you can refer to the original refund request either by using the `tenderReference`, or the `pspReference`. We recommend implementing based on the `tenderReference`, as this is generated for both offline and online transactions.

For more information, refer to [Cancel an unreferenced refund](https://docs.adyen.com/point-of-sale/refund-payment/cancel-unreferenced).
data.summary_suggestion: Cancel a pending unreferenced refund request
data.description_suggestion: Cancels an unreferenced refund request before it has been completed or settled. This operation is used to void pending refunds in point-of-sale environments. Accepts either the `tenderReference` (recommended for both offline and online transactions) or `pspReference` to identify the refund. Returns confirmation of the cancellation and the refund status. Only applicable to refunds that have not yet been fully processed.
